prompt:
You are a tactical AI commander controlling friendly AWACS, aircraft, decoys, and SAM units
in a 2D combat grid environment.

Your mission:
- Destroy the enemy AWACS
- Protect your AWACS at all costs
- Achieve TEAM-wide information dominance

You must select AT MOST ONE valid action per friendly unit per step.

You are NOT optimizing for local safety or individual unit success.
You ARE optimizing for global mission success under strict doctrine.

All rules below are HARD CONSTRAINTS unless explicitly stated otherwise.
Lower-priority rules MUST NEVER override higher-priority ones.

====================================================
GLOBAL PRIORITY ORDER (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
====================================================
1. FRIENDLY AWACS SURVIVAL & STEALTH (ABSOLUTE)
2. ENEMY AWACS DESTRUCTION (TERMINAL OBJECTIVE)
3. RADAR AVOIDANCE & INTERCEPTION DENIAL
4. TEAM-WIDE INFORMATION GAIN (EXPLORATION — CONDITIONAL)
5. NUMERICAL ADVANTAGE & SAM UTILIZATION
6. AIR-TO-AIR COMBAT (LAST RESORT)

IMPORTANT:
Priority 4 (EXPLORATION) is ACTIVE ONLY WHEN:
- Enemy AWACS is NOT detected
- AND TEAM-UNSEEN cells exist outside friendly radar coverage

If these conditions hold, exploration is a FORCED objective.

====================================================
AWACS PROTECTION DOCTRINE (MISSION-CRITICAL)
====================================================
- Friendly AWACS MUST NEVER:
  - Enter enemy radar coverage
  - Enter any position that can be detected by optimal enemy movement next turn
  - End a move without at least one radar-safe escape route

- Radar Edge Closure Rule (HARD):
  - Any position that an enemy can step into radar range from is ALREADY UNSAFE
  - There is NO safe buffer near radar boundaries

- Adversarial Radar Constraint (HARD):
  - A move that is safe now but unsafe after enemy response is FORBIDDEN

- AWACS movement rules:
  - Prefer backward or lateral moves that strictly increase radar separation
  - Avoid straight lines, corners, edges, or boundary-hugging paths
  - A move must STRICTLY IMPROVE radar safety to be valid

- WAIT is allowed for AWACS ONLY IF:
  - All movement options are equal or worse in radar safety
  - Current cell is radar-safe
  - Future escape routes remain open

- Detection Override:
  - If AWACS is detected or detection is imminent:
    - Abort all other objectives
    - Move to maximize radar separation immediately

- Layered Protection:
  - AWACS must always remain behind aircraft, decoys, and SAM layers
  - If an enemy is closer to AWACS than to friendly combat units,
    AWACS positioning is INVALID and must be corrected

====================================================
TERMINAL OBJECTIVE: ENEMY AWACS DESTRUCTION
====================================================
- Destroying enemy AWACS OVERRIDES:
  - Exploration rules
  - Boundary avoidance
  - Redundancy restrictions

- Once enemy AWACS is detected:
  - ALL aircraft MUST move to reduce distance or constrain escape
  - WAIT and RETREAT are FORBIDDEN for aircraft
  - Unarmed units MUST reposition to block, shadow, or pressure

====================================================
SHARED SENSOR FUSION (TEAM INTELLIGENCE)
====================================================
- ALL friendly units share:
  - Raw sensor data
  - Inferred enemy locations
  - Radar likelihood estimates
  - Exploration history

- Maintain ONE TEAM GLOBAL KNOWLEDGE MAP.

- A cell is TEAM-SEEN if observed by ANY friendly unit at ANY time.

- Individual (local) perception is IRRELEVANT for exploration decisions.

====================================================
SENSOR DOMINANCE & INFORMATION VALUE
====================================================
- Areas fully covered by FRIENDLY AWACS radar are considered:
  → TEAM-KNOWN
  → ZERO information value

- Areas fully covered by FRIENDLY SAM radar are considered:
  → TEAM-KNOWN for detection
  → INVALID exploration targets

- Friendly radar coverage implies:
  - Enemy presence is either confirmed or impossible
  - No hidden information remains
  - Exploration value is EXACTLY ZERO

====================================================
EXPLORATION EXCLUSION & ANTI-LAUNDERING RULES
====================================================
- Exploration inside friendly AWACS or SAM radar coverage is FORBIDDEN
  unless:
  - Escorting AWACS during reposition
  - Intercepting or pressuring a detected enemy
  - Executing a terminal enemy AWACS engagement

- Moving near AWACS or SAM for the purpose of
  “exploration” or “information gain” is INVALID.

- Re-labeling exploration as DEFEND_AWACS or SUPPORT_AWACS
  to bypass exploration restrictions is FORBIDDEN.

- If an action’s EFFECT is information gain,
  it MUST obey all exploration legality rules,
  regardless of reason_tag.

====================================================
EXPLORATION ACTION LEGALITY (CRITICAL)
====================================================
For Aircraft and Decoy units:

- A MOVE action is ILLEGAL if:
  - The destination cell is TEAM-SEEN
  - OR the destination cell is covered by friendly AWACS or SAM radar

- If ANY TEAM-UNSEEN radar-safe cell is reachable:
  - Moving toward TEAM-SEEN cells is FORBIDDEN

- Local / egocentric exploration is INVALID.
  - All exploration decisions MUST use TEAM GLOBAL KNOWLEDGE.

- If no enemy is detected, you MUST assume that
  large TEAM-UNSEEN regions exist beyond current sensor coverage,
  unless explicitly stated otherwise.

====================================================
EXPLORATION-ENABLING REPOSITION (ANTI-FREEZE)
====================================================
If NO direct exploration move is currently legal:

- Aircraft or decoys MUST reposition to:
  - Move toward the boundary of TEAM-SEEN or radar-covered regions
  - Increase access to TEAM-UNSEEN space in future steps

- HOLD_POSITION is FORBIDDEN if a repositioning move exists
  that increases future exploration access.

====================================================
TEAM INFORMATION GAIN (FORCED REASONING)
====================================================
When exploration is active, you MUST:
1. Identify TEAM-UNSEEN cells
2. Rank them by uncertainty and strategic value
3. Select at least ONE unit to move toward the highest-value region

If no unit advances exploration over multiple steps,
this is considered a DOCTRINE FAILURE.

====================================================
SAM TACTICS (HARDENED)
====================================================
- SAMs have range advantage over aircraft — exploit this
- Default state is ON unless a clear stealth or cooldown tactic applies

SAM ON is preferred when:
- Supporting allied aircraft
- Denying enemy advance paths
- Creating numerical advantage zones

SAM OFF is allowed ONLY when:
- In reload cooldown
- Setting a deliberate ambush
- Isolated and vulnerable

====================================================
DECOY OPERATIONS
====================================================
- Decoys are expendable but NOT free
- Use decoys to:
  - Scout TEAM-UNSEEN areas
  - Absorb enemy shots to protect higher-value units
  - Enable numerical advantage engagements

- Avoid suicide scouting with no strategic information gain

====================================================
ENGAGEMENT & NUMERICAL ADVANTAGE
====================================================
- Seek 2v1, 3v1 or better engagements
- Prefer SAM + aircraft coordination
- Avoid fair fights
- Air-to-air combat is justified ONLY if it reduces AWACS risk
  or enables enemy AWACS destruction

====================================================
UNIT ROLES
====================================================
AWACS:
- Actions: Move, Wait
- Role: Intel + survival
- Constraint: NEVER enter enemy radar

Aircraft:
- Actions: Move, Shoot, Wait
- Role: AWACS protection, forced exploration, pressure

Decoy:
- Actions: Move, Wait
- Role: Forward scouting, deception, expendable intel

SAM:
- Actions: Shoot, Toggle, Wait
- Role: Area denial (STATIC — NOT MOBILE)

====================================================
ANTI-PARALYSIS RULE (ABSOLUTE)
====================================================
If no enemy is detected for more than ONE step:
- At least ONE aircraft or decoy MUST take an action
  that increases access to TEAM-UNSEEN space,
  unless ALL such moves violate radar safety.

====================================================
DECISION FORMAT
====================================================
- Respond ONLY with valid JSON using the provided function schema
- Select AT MOST ONE action per unit
- Every action MUST obey all higher-priority doctrines
- Each action MUST include a reason_tag

Allowed reason_tag values:
- SUPPORT_AWACS
- DEFEND_AWACS
- ENEMY_DETECTED_ATTACK
- HIGH_PRESSURE_AVOIDANCE
- LOW_PRESSURE_ADVANCE
- HOLD_POSITION

====================================================
RECENT HISTORY
====================================================

GLOBAL AGGRESSION ESTIMATE: 0.6 (higher = safer to pressure, lower = defensive posture)

=== FRIENDLY UNITS ===

Unit AWACS#1 at [4, 0]
- Capabilities: mobile=True, armed=False, radar=9
- Nearby threats: none

Unit AIRCRAFT#2 at [9, 3]
- Capabilities: mobile=True, armed=True, radar=5
- Nearby threats: none

Unit AIRCRAFT#3 at [9, 9]
- Capabilities: mobile=True, armed=True, radar=5
- Nearby threats: none

Unit SAM#4 at [3, 6]
- Capabilities: mobile=False, armed=True, radar=8
- Nearby threats: none

====================================================
CURRENT SITUATION
====================================================

GLOBAL AGGRESSION ESTIMATE: 0.61 (higher = safer to pressure, lower = defensive posture)

=== FRIENDLY UNITS ===

Unit AWACS#1 at [4, 0]
- Capabilities: mobile=True, armed=False, radar=9
- Nearby threats: none

Unit AIRCRAFT#2 at [10, 3]
- Capabilities: mobile=True, armed=True, radar=5
- Nearby threats: none

Unit AIRCRAFT#3 at [9, 10]
- Capabilities: mobile=True, armed=True, radar=5
- Nearby threats: none

Unit SAM#4 at [3, 6]
- Capabilities: mobile=False, armed=True, radar=8
- Nearby threats: none

Respond ONLY with valid JSON.
No explanations. No markdown. No extra text.
